B.a3v=new A.e1("Welcome!","This app teaches you how to build **finite automata**, **pushdown automata**, and **Turing machines** \u2014 the fundamental models of computation.\n\nEach level asks you to build an automaton that matches a target language. Follow these tutorials first to learn the tools, then dive in!",B.ck)
B.a3j=new A.ii(1,"addNode")
B.a3u=new A.e1("Adding States","**Double-tap** on any empty area of the canvas to create a new state (circle).\n\nStates represent positions your machine can be in while reading input. You can drag states around to arrange your diagram.",B.a3j)
B.a3l=new A.ii(2,"addTransition")
B.a3H=new A.e1("Drawing Transitions",'Hold **Shift** and drag from one state to another to draw a transition arrow.\n\nAfter drawing, **tap the label** on the arrow to set which input symbol it reads (e.g. "a", "b", "0", "1"). A single arrow can carry multiple symbols \u2014 separate them with commas.',B.a3l)
B.a3m=new A.ii(3,"setAccepting")
B.a3C=new A.e1("Accept States",'A state shown with a **double ring** is an accepting state \u2014 the machine accepts the input if it finishes in one of these.\n\nTo make a state accepting: **tap it** to open its menu, then toggle **"Accept"**.',B.a3m)
B.a3n=new A.ii(4,"setStartArrow")
B.a3t=new A.e1("The Start Arrow","Every automaton needs exactly **one start state** \u2014 the state it begins in.\n\nDrag the floating start arrow onto a state to set it as the start. If no start arrow is visible, use the **toolbar** to place one.",B.a3n)
B.a3s=new A.ii(9,"deleteMode")
B.a3I=new A.e1("Deleting Things","Made a mistake? Use the **trash-can** button in the toolbar to enter delete mode.\n\nIn delete mode, **tap** any state or transition arrow to remove it. Tap the trash-can again to exit delete mode.",B.a3s)
B.a3k=new A.ii(10,"checkAnswer")
B.a3z=new A.e1("Checking Your Answer",'When you think your automaton is correct, tap **"Check"** in the top-right corner.\n\nThe app will test your machine against the target language. If they match, the level is complete! If not, you\'ll see a **counterexample** \u2014 a string your machine handles differently from the target.',B.a3k)
