B.VM=new A.cb("intro_accept_a")
B.a3o=new A.ii(5,"dfaVsNfa")
B.a3D=new A.e1("Two Kinds of Automaton","Levels in this game are tagged **DFA** or **NFA** (or neither, for bosses).\n\n\u2022 A **DFA** (Deterministic Finite Automaton) must have exactly one transition per symbol per state.\n\u2022 An **NFA** (Nondeterministic Finite Automaton) can have zero, one, or many transitions for the same symbol.",B.a3o)
B.a3J=new A.e1("DFA Rules","For a valid DFA over alphabet {a, b}:\n\n1. Every state must have **exactly one** outgoing transition for each symbol.\n2. No \u03b5 (epsilon / free-jump) transitions are allowed.\n3. There must be exactly **one start state**.\n\nIf your submission violates any of these, the checker will tell you exactly which states are the problem.",B.ck)
B.a3E=new A.e1("NFA Rules","An NFA is more flexible \u2014 it **may** have:\n\n\u2022 Multiple outgoing arrows for the **same** symbol from one state\n\u2022 **\u03b5-transitions** (free jumps, drawn as arrows with no label)\n\u2022 States with **no** outgoing arrow for some symbol\n\nAn NFA accepts a string if **any** path through the machine leads to an accept state.",B.ck)
B.a3G=new A.e1('The "." (dot) Symbol','A transition labelled **"."** matches **any single symbol** from the alphabet.\n\nThis is a shorthand that saves you drawing one arrow per symbol. For example, a self-loop "." on a state means "stay here for any symbol".',B.ck)
B.a3p=new A.ii(6,"epsilonTransition")
B.a3A=new A.e1("Epsilon (\u03b5) Transitions","An **\u03b5-transition** (drawn without a label) is a free jump \u2014 the machine moves to the next state without consuming any input.\n\nIn the canvas, draw an arrow between two states and **clear the label** to create an \u03b5-transition. Only NFAs may use these.",B.a3p)
